headline: Levi Strauss Refocuses Portfolio As Target Partnership Widens Reach
summary: Levi Strauss (NYSE:LEVI) has sold its Dockers brand in Peru to Authentic Brands Group, adjusting its portfolio in that market. The company is expanding its relationship with Target, adding Levi's denim to 150 more Target stores. The Target partnership will also expand Levi's women's assortment, with changes planned for Spring 2026. Levi Strauss, trading at $22.16, has reported a 26.9% return over the past year and 35.8% over the past 3 years, with year-to-date performance of 6.4%. These...

headline: How Investors Are Reacting To Levi Strauss (LEVI) Expanding Its Levi’s Assortment Across More Target Stores
summary: In recent developments, Target expanded its long-running partnership with Levi Strauss & Co., bringing Levi’s denim to more than 1,000 Target stores by the end of 2026 and increasing its women’s assortment by nearly 20% with trend-focused, lifestyle-oriented pieces. This broader Target presence highlights how Levi’s is leaning on wholesale partnerships to extend brand reach even as it emphasizes Direct-to-Consumer growth. headline: Berkshire Hathaway earnings, February jobs report: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime Host Josh Lipton previews several of the biggest stories to come next week, including earnings results out from Berkshire Hathaway (BRK-B, BRK-A) this weekend, followed by companies like Costco (COST), Target (TGT), Okta (OKTA), and Broadcom (AVGO) throughout the week; the release of February's jobs report on Friday, March 6; and commentary from presidents of regional Federal Reserve banks. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.
